  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study in patients with obstructive sleep apnoea (OSA) and concomitant
      patent foramen ovale (PFO) is to assess the impact of percutaneous PFO closure on nocturnal
      hypoxemia and apnea/hypopnea, pulmonary and systemic artery pressure, endothelial function
      and arterial stiffness.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
